  "output": "Here's the comprehensive technical description of the debounce module:\n\n1. Overview:\nThe `debounce` module is a sequential circuit that implements a digital debouncer for mechanical switch inputs with configurable bit width.\n\n2. Functionality:\nThe module filters out contact bounce from mechanical switches by requiring stable input for 20ms before registering a state change. It detects rising edges on debounced inputs and generates corresponding single-clock-cycle pulses. The debounce period is controlled by a counter that runs at the system clock frequency.\n\n3. Interface:\n- Inputs:\n  - `clk` [1-bit]: System clock input\n  - `rst_n` [1-bit]: Active-low asynchronous reset\n  - `key` [N-bit]: Raw switch inputs to be debounced (width configurable via parameter N)\n  \n- Outputs:\n  - `key_pulse` [N-bit]: Pulse output indicating rising edge detection on debounced inputs\n\n4. Implementation:\n- Logic type: Sequential (synchronous with asynchronous reset)\n- Key operations:\n  - 19-bit counter (`cnt`) that creates 20ms timing window (value 19'h75601)\n  - Two-stage pipeline (`key_sec` and `key_sec_pre`) for edge detection\n  - Asynchronous reset initializes all registers\n- Special signals:\n  - Clock: `clk` (positive edge triggered)\n  - Reset: `rst_n` (asynchronous, active low)\n\n5. Technical Characteristics:\n- Bit widths:\n  - Parameter `N` defaults to 2 (configurable input/output width)\n  - Counter width: 19 bits (0-19'h75601 for 20ms @ 24MHz)\n  - Data paths: All signals maintain N-bit width except internal counter\n- Timing:\n  - 20ms debounce period (counter value 19'h75601)\n  - Output pulses are exactly 1 clock cycle wide\n  - Asynchronous reset to known state\n- Resource implications:\n  - Requires one 19-bit counter\n  - Two N-bit registers for pipeline\n  - Minimal combinational logic for edge detection\n  - Parameterized width allows scaling for multiple inputs",
